A close-up vintage photograph of a laptop keyboard from the mid-2000s era, warm sepia tones with slight film grain, focusing on the distinctive red rubber nub of a TrackPoint nestled between the G, H, and B keys, with fingertips hovering nearby in soft focus. The image has the aesthetic of a well-worn technology magazine spread, with rich shadows and nostalgic amber lighting suggesting late afternoon in a busy office. Scratches and subtle wear marks on the black keys convey years of faithful use, while the iconic red pointing stick stands out as a small but vibrant focal point against the muted surroundings.
